[3] Greece
Date: Sat 30 Dec 2017 02:03:24 EET
Source: Xinhua News Agency [edited]
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-12/30/c_136860578.htm


Greece is facing a measles epidemic this year [2017] with the number of reported cases tripling within 2 months, according to the national centre for the control and prevention of diseases (Keelpno) on [Fri 29 Dec 2017].

In late October [2017], the 1st casualty of the disease outbreak was a vaccinated Roma baby of 11 months. A total of 326 confirmed cases had been reported from the start of the year. By [28 Dec 2017], Keelpno confirmed 922 measles cases across the country.

Most cases, according to data, concerned Roma children, and people aged 25-44, who were not properly immunized against measles.

Since 2016 more than 19 000 cases have been reported across Europe, including 46 deaths of complications, experts noted.

Keelpno reiterated calls for prompt vaccination of people at risk.

[editor: Mu Xuequan]

