[4] Romania (Neamt county)
Date: Sat 30 Dec 2017
Source: Romania Insider [edited]
https://www.romania-insider.com/measles-takes-new-life-romania/


A 6 month old baby in the Neamt county, north eastern Romania, died of measles last week [week of 18 Dec 2017], according to the National Center for Surveillance and Control of Communicable Diseases (CNSCBT). It was the 37th demise recorded in Romania since the onset of the measles epidemic [in 2016]. According to specialists, the child was suffering from anemia and was not eligible for vaccination.

The number of people who got sick with measles has reached 12 279 since this epidemic started.

Most deaths, 9, were registered in the Timis county. Other 7 demises were recorded in Dolj county, whereas 6 were in Arad, 3 in Caras-Severin, 2 in Neamt, and 1 in Bihor, Brasov, Cluj, Calarasi, Satu Mare, Vaslui, Galati, Mures, and Bucharest.

Measles caused the death of people aged 3 weeks-39 years, who were unvaccinated. 15 of those who died had no health problems before measles.

